 bangkok, thailand (ap) _ thailand's criminal court has fined a law tutor who threw a bag of human excrement at the minister of commerce in 1994, the bangkok post reported friday. judge somchai panthmnopas imposed a 6,000-baht (dlrs 155) fine and a suspended one-year jail term on thanit suwanmena on thursday, the paper said. thanit hurled the bag of excrement at commerce minister uthai pimchaichon during a press conference in 1994. it exploded on impact when it hit uthai's face. the tutor said he was angry that uthai had reinstated a commerce ministry official accused of corruption. uthai</enamex> was one of the chief drafters of thailand</enamex>'s new constitution, which is designed to reduce corruption and increase civil rights. 